Another weekend is upon us and if you are still sleeping on this new film releases, you are on a long thing. We have gathered some new and exciting new films for you to watch to spice up your weekend. Check on them below: The Lion King characters | Photo – Metro Release date: July 19, 2019. Cast: Donald Glover, Beyoncé, James Earl Jones, Chiwetel Ejiofor, Billy Eichner, Seth Roger, John Kani, John Oliver, Keegan-Michael Key, Florence Kasumba, and Alfre Woodard Plot Summary: A photorealistic CGI remake of Disney’s 1994 animated film, about a lion cub named Simba who runs away into the Savannah after his evil uncle Scar kills his father and takes over the lion kingdom. Into The Ashes | Photo – Trailer Addict Release date: July 19, 2019. Cast: Luke Grimes, Robert Taylor, James Badge Dale, Frank Grillo, David Cade, Marguerite Moreau, Brady Smith, David Maldonado Plot Summary: Nick is an ex-con who is adjusting to a new job, a new wife and some semblance of normalcy in rural Alabama. When vengeful former associates track him down, he is soon forced back into the desperate and violent life that he thought he left behind. David Crosby – Remember My Name | Photo – Rock Cellar Magazine Release date: July 19, 2019. Cast: David Crosby Plot Summary: With unflinching honesty, self-examination, regret, fear, exuberance and an unshakable belief in family and the transformative nature of music, singer-songwriter David Crosby shares his often challenging journey. N.B: All release dates are U.S  release dates.